'''''Classic Star Wars: Devilworlds''''' is a two-part comic collection that is part of the ''[[Classic Star Wars]]'' series of comics and re-publishes several of the more obscure ''[[Star Wars]]'' tales by [[Alan Moore]], [[Steve Moore]], and [[Steve Parkhouse]] from [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] [[Star Wars (Marvel UK)|UK ''Star Wars'']] . The artwork has been colored, reformatted, and retouched by [[Dark Horse Comics]]. It is notable for featuring stories of ambiguous [[canon]]icity with several of the tales only much later being referenced and brought into the official continuity.<ref name="CSWE">Characters and events from ''[[Dark Lord's Conscience]]'', ''[[Blind Fury!]]'', ''[[The Pandora Effect]]'' and ''[[Tilotny Throws a Shape]]'' have all been referenced in ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'', elevating the stories to [[Canon|C-Canon]].</ref>

The series is composed of two issues released between August [[1996]] and September [[1996]].

